# Reflex Frontend Rules (archived product)

> **`finance_manager_reflex` is archived (2026-04-30).** New work belongs in **`finance_manager_web/`** (see ecosystem `AGENTS.md` and `plans/cursor/strategic-roadmap-reframe-53be/`). Apply this file only when touching the historical Reflex tree.

Apply these rules when editing **legacy** Reflex frontend code.

## Frontend Implementation Expectations

- Keep UI behavior changes aligned with backend contracts and production intent.
- Prefer reusable UI/state patterns over one-off page-specific logic.
- Keep presentation concerns separate from data-fetch and transformation concerns.

## Tracking and Documentation

- Record meaningful frontend behavior changes in the relevant changelog/docs.
- For significant feature work, keep plan artifacts up to date and archive completed plans.
- When implementation decisions affect deployment readiness, note the production impact in project docs.

## Collaboration Defaults

- Leave clear implementation notes where a choice is non-obvious for other contributors.
- Escalate missing dependency/tooling needs when they would improve reliability or maintainability.
